Even so, people in my guild can't understand why I used to go to the flameboard to blow off steam.  I have over 83 days played and I guarantee you that 50 of those were spent sitting in North Freeport staring at a wall listening to someone with a problem.  It's just something I was good at.<br>
<br>
Amazing how little that means when it all boils down, how easy it is to forget that someone sacrificed their time to be there for you... I learned too late that 99% of the good things you do for people are forgotten or dismissed. <p><center>
