<br>
But to be honest, I'd be pretty goddamn angry too! This game isn't my life, I play it for fun and relaxation, how DARE they, a complete stranger, start laying their life story and troubles on me just like that? You go golfing, and get paired up with someone who lays that story on you, yes, you'll obviously feel sympathy, but jesus, WTF? And there are kids in the game too. <br>
<br>
I know I sound like a cynic and a big meanie. I'm not. I'm not saying what you did was wrong of course. It was right, potentially a fantastic thing, but if that's your thing, there are volunteer services you can sign up for, to help people who are depressed. And if you need help, there are people you can call.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/usalveghostwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salve Ghostwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/28/01 12:15:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Don't Cry Wolf</span><hr size=1> Heh, I haven't voted because it generally depends on the person; if it's some complete stranger, I would think, &quot;Why are they confiding in ME when they have friends in the game?&quot; If it's someone I know, at least within the game, I give my thoughts but I don't expect any imbedded advice to be heeded.<br>
<br>
I must warn people, however, not to cry wolf.  I used to MUD alot years ago, and one mudder thought he would get sympathy by telling everyone he was going to kill himself.  He cited real problems that he had, failing grades and a recent breakup with his long-time girlfriend; he was utterly convincing.  He was, though, just screwing around.  Unfortunately for him, the sysop fell for it hook, line, and sinker, and contacted the police.  The kid was taken, struggling, out of his bedroom, wrestled into a straightjacket, drugged, and carted off for two weeks of psychic evaluation. <br>
<br>
The police, his parents, everyone bought into it.  The kid was released after two weeks but placed into &quot;counseling&quot;, where he was supposed to try and deal with a problem that didn't exist.  This happened near the end of a school year, and any chance he had of saving his grades went down the toilet.  Ditto the ex-girlfriend, whose parents now considered him an unstable danger to their daughter.  This kid's life was turned upside down by threatening suicide online.  <br>
<br>
If some woman wants to tell people that her husband is beating her, and that she would show undying devotion to someone who would rescue her, she'd better be prepared for someone to show up on her doorstep and club her husband to death.  It can happen.  Of course, maybe that's what they're all hoping .... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ucogito.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cogito</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord of the Whacky Woondarland</span><br>  Posts: 444<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/28/01 12:47:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://server49.hypermart.net/voxton/flash/mouse.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Don't Cry Wolf</span><hr size=1> Salve, I'd never think anyone could get me to laugh on a thread like this, but you did it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Well said, and damn funny too. Not easy to make light of such a dark situation. <br>
